From 9ce36dddd5df3f7dfbdc9c73380fc0e43e2e5e5d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aaron Forinton <aaron.forinton@poly-ai.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Apr 2026 15:39:37 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] docs: add Agents API reference with full endpoint scaffolding
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Introduces the new Agents API (aka builder / Agent Studio APIs) — the
write-side REST surface for creating, configuring, and deploying agents
programmatically.

What's in this PR:

- api-reference/agents/: new openapi.json (47 endpoints across 9 tags)
  and introduction.mdx explaining the resource model, base URL, auth,
  quick-start, and how the API differs from the Conversations API.
- api-reference/agents/endpoint/: one MDX per endpoint, organized into
  subfolders by resource (agents, branches, behavior, knowledge-base,
  variants, deployments, connectors, phone-numbers, real-time-configs).
- docs.json: new 'Agents API' group in the API reference tab with nine
  nested subgroups for clean sidebar navigation.
- api-reference/introduction.mdx: rewritten top section to frame the
  three API families (build & deploy, runtime & data, monitoring) and
  draw a clear Agents-vs-Conversations distinction.
- Feature-doc cross-references with curl + Python examples in:
  environments-and-versions, variant-management, telephony,
  managed-topics, agent-settings/introduction, agent-settings/rules,
  telephony/how-to-buy-number, api/introduction.

Debug Chat is out of scope for this PR (no spec yet). Will land in a
follow-up when the OpenAPI definition is available.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
